docs.name: GNI - Current Prices, National Currency - Liberia
docs.description: Liberia GNI at current prices - national currency. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. For more about the National Accounts Main Aggregates database, see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/introduction.asp.  To see country-specific metadata, see <a href=http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=L>http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=L.

docs.name: GDP - Current Prices, National Currency - El Salvador
docs.description: El Salvador GDP by Type of Expenditure at current prices - national currency. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. For more about the National Accounts Main Aggregates database, see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/introduction.asp.  To see country-specific metadata, see <a href=http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=E>http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=E.

docs.name: GNI - Current Prices, National Currency - Mali
docs.description: Mali GNI at current prices - national currency. The National Accounts Main Aggregates database is produced and maintained by the Economic Statistics Branch of the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD), with input from the UNSD, international organizations, and the national statistical agencies of more than 200 countries.  The database consists of a complete and consistent record of the main National Accounts of each UN member state, from 1970 onwards.  Records are based on official country data reported to the UNSD, supplemented with estimates for any years and countries with incomplete or inconsistent information.  The database is updated in December of each year. For more about the National Accounts Main Aggregates database, see http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/introduction.asp.  To see country-specific metadata, see <a href=http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=M>http://unstats.un.org/unsd/snaama/metasearch.asp?letter=M.

FAOSTAT provides access to over 3 million time-series and cross sectional data relating to food and agriculture,for 200 countries and more than 200 primary products.

docs.description: Land Usage Statistics for United Arab Emirates.  Sources: Millennium Development Goals Database and FAOSTAT Database.  The Millennium Development Goals Database is compiled by the Inter-Agency and Expert Group (IAEG), coordinated by the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD).  FAOSTAT provides access to over 3 million time-series and cross sectional data relating to food and agriculture,for 200 countries and more than 200 primary products.

docs.description: Land Usage Statistics for United Republic of Tanzania.  Sources: Millennium Development Goals Database and FAOSTAT Database.  The Millennium Development Goals Database is compiled by the Inter-Agency and Expert Group (IAEG), coordinated by the United Nations Statistics Division (UNSD).  FAOSTAT provides access to over 3 million time-series and cross sectional data relating to food and agriculture,for 200 countries and more than 200 primary products.

The United Nations Commodity Trade Statistics Database (UN Comtrade) provides a considerable amount of data on trade from over 140 countries starting in 1962.
